   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Instructions to reproduce:

* Have JS enabled in your browser
* Go to <a href="http://openhatch.org/missions/tar">http://openhatch.org/missions/tar</a>
* Complete all the sections
* Go back to <a href="http://openhatch.org/missions/tar">http://openhatch.org/missions/tar</a>
* Click the JavaScript-y link to reset the mission's state
* Notice the checkmarks are still dark green

Ta-da, the bug.

However, for what it's worth: If you reload the page, the checkmarks are
properly not dark green anymore.

Karen, if you agree with this assessment of the bug, I know the fix (to adjust
the onclick handler in JS to mark the checkboxes as pale by changing their CSS
class).</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
